On due consideration to the submissions advanced, perusal of the record so also the fact that charge-sheet in the matter has been filed, applicant has cooperated in the investigation and he shall cooperate in the trial, there is no corroborative evidence for the offences alleged, appicant is not a previous convict, prima facie dispute appears to be matrimonial in nature the interim protection granted by this Court vide order dated 13.08.2024 is made absolute in view of dictum of Apex Court in re: 
Sushila Aggarwal Vs. State (NCT of Delhi
)-2020 SCC online SC 98.
